reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not a good buy.
reviews.reviewText: I had to return these headphones the same day I received them. The sound quality is ok but not great at all, it sounds muffled a bit. The headphones feel very cheap and the ear portion broke as soon as I tried them on. I guess I’ll have to search elsewhere.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Remember they are $20 bucks
reviews.reviewText: So I’ve really wanted some bigger headphones and I absolutely without a doubt do not want to spend $500 for a set.I use them for the gym and they serve the purpose. Can I hear things around me? sometimes.. they aren’t sound proof. Is the sound quality fine? Yes, no crazy static or weird noises just clear music. They Bluetooth connect easily. They are light but definitely feel cheaply made .. again this brings me back to they are $20 headphones. So in this sense you are 100% getting what you pay for. The ear pieces fit comfortably over my ears and there is no weird pressure or discomfort.I’m satisfied with my purchase and feel as though I spent my $20 wisely. If you are looking for something to listen to music to while you workout and not do anything spectacular these are it.
